Description of the data structure DS:
\begin{itemize}
\item A perfect hash table keyed by the elements’ values. For each element, also store its \(\operatorname{rank}\) (order statistic).
\end{itemize}

Description of the construction:
\begin{itemize}
\item Sort the array, \(O(n \log n)\), to determine the \(\operatorname{rank}\) of each element.
\item Insert the elements into the perfect hash; \(O(n)\) on average.
\end{itemize}

How to sort using the data structure:
\begin{itemize}
\item For each element in \(S\), retrieve its order statistic (\(\operatorname{rank}\)).
\item Sort \(S\) according to these order statistics using CountSort.
\end{itemize}

